Femi Fani-Kayode, a former Aviation Minister, has said the All Progressives Congress, APC, would defeat the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, in 2023. Fani-Kayode made the remark while congratulating Bola Tinubu for emerging as APC presidential candidate. He noted that under Tinubu’s leadership, Nigeria shall grow in strength. In a Facebook post, the APC chieftain urged other Presidential aspirants to support Tinubu ahead of the 2023 election. According to Fani-Kayode: “I congratulate Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu on a historic victory at the Convention of our great party. “I have no doubt that he will lead us to a resounding victory against the opposition PDP next year and that under his leadership our country shall go from strength to strength. “I also commend the courage of all those other presidential aspirants that ran in this race and that displayed such commitment and loyalty to the party. “I urge that we all come together as one, support our candidate and ensure that we defeat the PDP next year in the presidential election.”